T-ALL Visualization

Yuting Dai

2022-11-19

Data description

In this tutorial, we provided three demo files demo.meta.data, demo.mut.data and demo.exp.data.

  • demo.meta.data: storing clinical information and genetic features of T-ALL patients. In the file demo.meta.data, rows indicate patients and columns indicate features (such as age, gender).

  • demo.mut.data: mutations profile of T-ALL patients.

  • demo.exp.data: storing expression profile of T-ALL patients. In this file, rows indicate the expression level of genes (genes with top variance) and columns indicate patients. In both of the two files, patients were ranked in the same order.

All demo data in this tutorial could be downloaded via GitHub: https://github.com/ytdai/ytdai.github.io/tree/master/T_ALL_viz/data

Dimensionality reduction

##################
# definition of colors 
color.group <- c("#FD6AB0","#AA5700","#F48326","#FFD711","#9BD53F","#00AE4C","#00C1E3","#007DDB","#8538D1","#D01910")
names(color.group) <- c(paste0("G", 1:10))

color.etp <- c("#D01910","#00599F","#CCCCCC")
names(color.etp) <- c("ETP","notETP","undefine")

color.tcell <- c("#B2DF8A", "#33A02C","#1F78B4","#A6761D","#E31A1C","#CCCCCC")
names(color.tcell) <- c("Procortical","Precortical","Cortical","Postcortical","Medullary","undefine")

##################
# Run tsne
perplexity = 15
theta = 0.2
set.seed(1)
tsne.out <- Rtsne(t(demo.exp.data), perplexity = perplexity, theta = theta, dims = 2)
colnames(tsne.out$Y) <- c("tSNE1", "tSNE2")

plot.info <- as.data.frame(cbind(tsne.out$Y, demo.meta.data[, c("ID","Group","Age","Gender")]))
p <- ggscatter(plot.info, 
               x = "tSNE1", y = "tSNE2",
               color = "Group", fill = "Group",
               palette = color.group,
               xlab = "tSNE-1", ylab = "tSNE-2")
p <- p + theme_few()
p

##################
# Run PCA
res.pca.comp <- prcomp(demo.exp.data, scale = TRUE)

plot.data <- as.data.frame(res.pca.comp$rotation[, 1:10])
plot.data$ID = rownames(plot.data)
sum(plot.data$ID != demo.meta.data$ID)
## [1] 0
plot.data$Group <- demo.meta.data$Group

p <- ggscatter(plot.data, 
               x = "PC1", y = "PC2",
               color = "Group", fill = "Group",
               palette = color.group,
               xlab = "PC-1", ylab = "PC-2")
p <- p + theme_few()
p

##################
# Diffusion map
dm.data <- as.matrix(scale(t(demo.exp.data)))
sigma.use <- find_sigmas(dm.data, verbose = FALSE)@optimal_sigma
plot.data <- DiffusionMap(dm.data, sigma = sigma.use, k = 10, 
                          density_norm = TRUE, distance = "euclidean",
                          n_pcs = 30 )
## as(<dsCMatrix>, "dgTMatrix") is deprecated since Matrix 1.5-0; do as(as(., "generalMatrix"), "TsparseMatrix") instead
colnames(plot.data@eigenvectors) <- paste0("DC_", seq_len(ncol(plot.data@eigenvectors)))

plot.data <- as.data.frame(plot.data@eigenvectors)
plot.data$ID <- demo.meta.data$ID
plot.data$Group <- demo.meta.data$Group
p <- ggscatter(plot.data, 
               x = "DC_1", y = "DC_2",
               color = "Group", fill = "Group",
               palette = color.group,
               xlab = "DC-1", ylab = "DC-2")
p <- p + theme_few()
p

plot.data$color <- color.group[as.numeric(as.factor(plot.data$Group))]
scatterplot3d(x = plot.data$DC_1, 
              y = plot.data$DC_3, 
              z = plot.data$DC_2,
              color = plot.data$color,
              pch = 16, cex.symbols = 1,
              scale.y = 0.7, angle = 120,
              xlab = "DC_1", ylab = "DC_3", zlab = "DC_2",
              col.axis = "#444444", col.grid = "#CCCCCC")

Config file could be downloaded via config_file_content

##################
# heatmap
config_file_content <- "data/config.allsample.fig.basic.yaml"

config_file_content <- read.config(config_file_content)
config_file_content <- gvmapModAttr(attr_name = "legend_num", value = 2, config_file = config_file_content)
config_file_content <- gvmapModAttr(attr_name = "heatmap_num", value = 0, config_file = config_file_content)
config_file_content <- gvmapModAttr(attr_name = "percentage", value = 0.1, target = "heatmap_1", config_file = config_file_content)
config_file_content <- gvmapModAttr(attr_name = "map_order", 
                                    value = c("legend_1","legend_2"),
                                    config_file = config_file_content)


leg_value_col_1 <- c("Group", "Age", "Gender")
leg_value_name_1 <- c("Subgroup", "Age", "Gender")
leg_value_1 <- data.frame(name = leg_value_name_1,
                          color = c("pool_col","pool_age_col", "pool_gender_col"),
                          column = match(leg_value_col_1, colnames(demo.mut.data)))
config_file_content <- gvmapModAttr(target = "legend_1", attr_name = "legend", value = leg_value_1, config_file = config_file_content)


leg_value_col_2 <- c("NOTCH1","FBXW7","PHF6","PTEN","DNM2","NRAS","JAK3","BCL11B","USP7","GATA3",
                     "NOTCH_sig","Epi","IF","PI3K","JAK_STAT","RAS_sig","Translation","CellCycle","Other")
leg_value_2 <- data.frame(name = leg_value_col_2,
                          color = "mutation_col",
                          column = match(leg_value_col_2, colnames(demo.mut.data)))
config_file_content <- gvmapModAttr(target = "legend_2", attr_name = "legend", value = leg_value_2, config_file = config_file_content)

output_svg_name <- paste0("data/mutation.pathway.svg")

gvmap(legend_data = demo.mut.data,
      config_file = config_file_content,
      output_svg_name = output_svg_name,
      stroke_width = 0,
      dend_stroke_width = 1,
      frame_stroke_width = 1,
      sample_span = 2,
      group_span = 5,
      sample_font_size = 2,
      output_group_info = T,
      convert_pdf = T,
      plot_height = 1000)
